sentences.english: An anaconda in the Llanos of Venezuela.
sentences.chinese: 委内瑞拉大草原上的水蟒。

sentences.english: The Bolivarian leader's vaunted popularity tumbles.
sentences.chinese: 委内瑞拉玻利瓦尔共和国领导人所吹嘘的声望猛跌。

sentences.english: The son of a Venezuelan aristocrat, Bol var received a European education.
sentences.chinese: 是委内瑞拉贵族后裔，在欧洲受教育。

sentences.english: Venezuelan politics have been very complicated lately.
sentences.chinese: 委内瑞拉的政治最近很纷杂。

sentences.english: Venezuela has one of the highest rates of cosmetic surgery in the world.
sentences.chinese: 委内瑞拉是全世界整容手术率最高的国家之一。

sentences.english: We both think it’s dangerous to return to Venezuela as a same-sex married couple.
sentences.chinese: 我们都觉得作为同性伴侣回到委内瑞拉会很危险。

sentences.english: There is nothing in China to match the Venezuelan orchestral revolution.
sentences.chinese: 中国也没法和委内瑞拉革命相提并论。

sentences.english: Watch out of Venezuela on the critically endangered leatherback turtles.
sentences.chinese: 请关注委内瑞拉极度濒危的棱皮龟。

sentences.english: It's for volleyball, tomorrow evening. China vs Venezuela.
sentences.chinese: 就明天晚上的，男排，中国对委内瑞拉。

sentences.english: The first to do so were Brazil and Venezuela in 2005.
sentences.chinese: 2005年，巴西和委内瑞拉在这方面一马当先。

sentences.english: His name was Nando, and he was from Venezuela.
sentences.chinese: 他名叫南多，来自委内瑞拉。

sentences.english: He has voyaged through places like Venezuela and Peru.
sentences.chinese: 他已经航行经过像委内瑞拉和秘鲁这样的地方。

sentences.english: As evidence he offers the contrasting experiences of Singapore and Venezuela.
sentences.chinese: 他给出了新加坡和委内瑞拉的下例子来证明这一点。

sentences.english: Si ella no hubiera venido a Venezuela, habría ido a Perú.
sentences.chinese: 如果她没有来委内瑞拉，可能去了秘鲁。

sentences.english: Venezuela's commitment to closing down got them into difficulties within the first ten minutes.
sentences.chinese: 委内瑞拉对逼抢的投入让自己在前10分钟遇到难题。
